{"title":"Peonies","author":{"name":"Mary Oliver"},"publishDate":"2010-12-18","lines":[{"line":"This morning the green fists of the peonies are getting ready","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"to break my heart","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"as the sun rises,","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"as the sun strokes them with his old, buttery fingers","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"and they open —","stanza":2,"number":5},{"line":"pools of lace,","stanza":2,"number":6},{"line":"white and pink —","stanza":2,"number":7},{"line":"and all day the black ants climb over them,","stanza":2,"number":8},{"line":"boring their deep and mysterious holes","stanza":3,"number":9},{"line":"into the curls,","stanza":3,"number":10},{"line":"craving the sweet sap,","stanza":3,"number":11},{"line":"taking it away","stanza":3,"number":12},{"line":"to their dark, underground cities —","stanza":4,"number":13},{"line":"and all day","stanza":4,"number":14},{"line":"under the shifty wind,","stanza":4,"number":15},{"line":"as in a dance to the great wedding,","stanza":4,"number":16},{"line":"the flowers bend their bright bodies,","stanza":5,"number":17},{"line":"and tip their fragrance to the air,","stanza":5,"number":18},{"line":"and rise,","stanza":5,"number":19},{"line":"their red stems holding","stanza":5,"number":20},{"line":"all that dampness and recklessness","stanza":6,"number":21},{"line":"gladly and lightly,","stanza":6,"number":22},{"line":"and there it is again —","stanza":6,"number":23},{"line":"beauty the brave, the exemplary,","stanza":6,"number":24},{"line":"blazing open.","stanza":7,"number":25},{"line":"Do you love this world?","stanza":7,"number":26},{"line":"Do you cherish your humble and silky life?","stanza":7,"number":27},{"line":"Do you adore the green grass, with its terror beneath?","stanza":7,"number":28},{"line":"Do you also hurry, half-dressed and barefoot, into the garden,","stanza":8,"number":29},{"line":"and softly,","stanza":8,"number":30},{"line":"and exclaiming of their dearness,","stanza":8,"number":31},{"line":"fill your arms with the white and pink flowers,","stanza":8,"number":32},{"line":"with their honeyed heaviness, their lush trembling,","stanza":9,"number":33},{"line":"their eagerness","stanza":9,"number":34},{"line":"to be wild and perfect for a moment, before they are","stanza":9,"number":35},{"line":"nothing, forever?","stanza":9,"number":36}]}